claim.claim-text:
1. A gas hydrate conversion system, the system comprising:
a floating factory comprising:
one or more heat exchange assemblies;
one or more heat pump assemblies;
furnace adapted to disassociate one mole of methane into two moles of hydrogen and one mole of carbon; and
an engine;

an appendage for harvesting a gas hydrate from an oceanic hydrate deposit;
one or more storage tanks; and
a solar energy apparatus including a light conduit, the light conduit having reflective walls to provide high-intensity delivery of solar energy to the oceanic hydrate deposit.

5. The conversion system of claim 1, wherein the appendage for harvesting a gas hydrate further comprises:
a heat distributor for delivering warm water to the oceanic hydrate deposit;
a moveable pickup bell for capturing the gas hydrates from an inner capture zone;
an outer flexible skirt for capturing the gas hydrates from an outer capture zone; and
a hydrate conduit that carries the gas hydrates to the floating factory.
